The paper deals with private information retrieval (PIR) schemes, which are typically studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR) communities. The paper also involves coding theory, as it considers coded PIR schemes, which suggests a possible fit in the cs.DS (data structures and algorithms) category. The paper also discusses the capacity of PIR schemes, which is a fundamental concept in information theory and communication complexity, and may be relevant to the cs.CC (computational complexity) category. Finally, the paper deals with practical aspects of PIR schemes, which may be relevant to the cs.SI (social and information networks) category.
